    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chicken parcel[s]</strong> to one side of a baking tray and add the <strong>chopped sweet potato</strong> and <strong>onion quarters</strong> to the other side (cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 trays!)</p><p>Drizzle <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over the chopped sweet potato and onion quarters and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-30 min or until the sweet potato is starting to crisp and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
